* **Count & Layers:** The structure uses 8 blocks and has 3 layers.
* **Spatial Relationships:** The bottom layer consists of two identical red blocks (index 2) placed side-by-side.  The second layer is composed of a yellow block (index 7) positioned centrally atop the red blocks. The third layer features a green block (index 5) to the left, a blue block (index 4) in the center, and another blue block (index 10) to the right, all sitting atop the yellow block. Finally, a smaller orange block (index 15) is placed on top of the right blue block.

    * One green block (index 5)

    * One orange triangular block (index 15)
